1
00:00:01,700 --> 00:00:04,800
在2007的五月 Lily阿姨和Marshall叔叔结婚了
In May of 2007, Aunt Lily and Uncle Marshall got married

2
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:08,200
就在纽约州北部具有历史意义的 Van Smoot House
at the historic Van Smoot House in upstate New York.

3
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:11,700
哇，好漂亮，Lily
Wow, it's beautiful, Lily.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,100
没错，就跟我一直想要的一样
Yeah. It's just how I always pictured it.

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,000
最好你本来就这么想
Well, that was a load of crap.

6
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,900
孩子们，当你要结婚了 你会学到宝贵的一课
You see, kids, when you get married, you learn a hard lesson.

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,200
你一开始打算办的婚礼 最终大都不会成真
The wedding you set out to have is almost never the wedding you end up with.

8
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:26,500
[婚礼前8个月] 所以，我们决定办个小型的户外婚礼
So, we've decided on a small, outdoor wedding,

9
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,800
只请亲人和比较亲密的朋友
just family and close friends.

10
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:30,700
不超过25人
No more than 25 people

11
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,100
在某个漂亮的花园
in a beautiful garden somewhere,

12
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,300
也许当我们走在红毯上时
maybe an acoustic guitar playing

13
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:37,100
可以用原音吉他伴奏
while we walk down the aisle.

14
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,800
也许你们已知道有谁到了法院
And maybe you already know someone who went down to the courthouse

15
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,600
注册成为司仪
and registered as an officiant

16
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,600
他或者她，还是他--
so that he or she-- he--

17
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:45,200
可以主持仪式
could perform the ceremony.

18
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:48,200
但你恨婚姻，你怎么会想主持婚礼？
But you hate marriage. Why do you want to perform the ceremony?

19
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:51,600
因为那会在无声无息下 灌输一个想法到每个在场的女性脑中
Because it subtly implants in the mind of every woman there

20
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:53,000
那就是当我问什么问题时
that when I ask a question,

21
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:54,600
都要说 "我愿意"
you say, "I do."

22
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:56,800
没错
Yeah.

23
00:00:57,800 --> 00:00:59,200
[婚礼前6个月] 你越接近那个大日子
The closer you get to the big day,

24
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,500
就会做出越多的让步
the more concessions you make.

25
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,800
太好了，我妈要我邀请Lessners一家
Great. Now my mom's making me invite the Lessners.

26
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:07,000
那会让宾客数到达3位数
This puts our numbers in the triple digits.

27
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:12,000
哇，我想有时Lessner反而代表"比较多" (Less是较少之意)
Wow. I guess sometimes, Lessner is more... ner.

28
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:14,600
你知道有时候"较少反而是较多" 是怎么样的情况
You know how like sometimes less is more.

29
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,800
没错，现在就是了，是吧，宝贝？
Yeah. This is one of those times, sweetie?

30
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:21,300
你知道吗？没关系 这只代表这会是个有点大的户外婚礼
You know what? That's okay. It'll be a slightly big outdoor wedding.

31
